Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Meatballs and Bacon ==

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @ginger, garlic & lemongrass puree{15%g}, @salt{¼%tsp} and @water{1%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British beef mince{240%g}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs onto one side of a large baking tray. Lay the @British streaky bacon{4} rashers on the other side.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until both are browned and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

== Sambal Mayo and Slaw ==

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

In a medium bowl, combine the @sambal paste{30%g} and @mayonnaise{64%g}. Set aside.

> Use less sambal if you'd prefer things milder.

Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} down through the middle (but not all the way through).

When everything's almost ready, pop the buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Once the buns are warmed, transfer to your plates and spread each with a spoonful of sambal mayo.

Pop the @coleslaw mix{120%g} into the bowl with the remaining sambal mayo, then add half the coriander and toss together. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When everything's ready, add some sambal slaw to the buns.

Line each side with a bacon rasher, then spoon in the meatballs. Drizzle with the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} and sprinkle with the remaining coriander.

Serve on plates with the chips and remaining slaw alongside. Enjoy!